Install Ansbile
  Windows 10
    Install Ubunto Bash Shell 
      http://www.howtogeek.com/249966/how-to-install-and-use-the-linux-bash-shell-on-windows-10/
    Follow Ubunto instructions below

  Mac
    Install Xcode
    $ sudo easy_install pip
    $ sudo pip install ansible --quiet

  Redhat/Centos
    $ sudo yum install ansible

  Ubunto
    $ sudo apt-get install software-properties-common
    $ sudo apt-add-repository ppa:ansible/ansible
    $ sudo apt-get update
    $ sudo apt-get install ansible

  Other Platforms
    http://docs.ansible.com/ansible/intro_installation.html



Setup SSH Keys on Mac and copy to RaspberryPi units

1.  Run ssh-keygen and then copy new keys to rasppi
    mac%> cd ~/.ssh
    mac%> ssh-keygen -t rsa -C 'michael.johnson@netapp.com'
    [OPTIONAL] mac%> ssh-keygen -t rsa -C 'michael.johnson@netapp.com' -f id_ansible

2.    [repeat 'ssh-copy-id ' step for all raspberrypi units]
    mac%> ssh-copy-id pi@10.69.69.xx
    mac%> ping pi@10.69.69.xx    => no password should be required

3.  Ping test using Ansible
    mac%> ansible all -m ping --inventory-file=ansible_hosts -u pi
    [OPTIONAL] mac%> ansible all -m ping --inventory-file=ansible_hosts -u pi --private-key=~/.ssh/id_ansible


4.  Run apt-get update
    mac%> ansible all -a "sudo apt-get update" -f 2 -u pi --inventory-file=ansible_hosts
    [OPTIONAL] mac%> ansible all -a "sudo apt-get update" -f 2 -u pi --inventory-file=ansible_hosts --private-key=~/.ssh/id_ansible

5.  Run setup playbook.yml
    mac%> ansible-playbook playbook.yml -i hosts --become
